Program: Outlook
Title: Reverend Rose Hudson-Wilkin
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p008rnvs
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 30 Jul 2010
ROSE HUDSON-WILKIN Born and raised in Jamaica, the Reverend Rose Hudson-Wilkin has made history as the first black woman to be appointed Chaplain to the Speaker of the House of Commons. Her other role is as a vicar in Hackney, one of London's poorest boroughs. She is also seen as a leading contender to become one of the first women bishops in the Anglican Church. Show less